    <main class="container">
        <div class="doc-grid">
            <aside class="sidebar">
                <nav>
                    <ul>
                        <li><a href="installation.html">Getting Started</a></li>
                        <li><a href="basic-types.html">Basic Types</a></li>
                        <li><a href="functions.html">Functions</a></li>
                        <li><a href="#" class="active">Garbage Collection</a></li>
                        <li><a href="generics.html">Generics</a></li>
                        <li><a href="concurrency.html">Concurrency</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </nav>
            </aside>

            <article class="content">
                <section class="intro">
                    <div class="tag-container">
                        <span class="tag">Core Feature</span>
                        <span class="tag">Memory Vibes</span>
                        <span class="tag">No Cap</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="lead">CURSED comes with a fire 🔥 garbage collector so you can focus on the sigma grindset and not waste time on deleting stuff.</p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>The Tea on Garbage Collection</h2>
                    <p>Garbage collection in CURSED is giving main character energy with these features:</p>
                    <ul class="vibe-list">
                        <li><span class="emoji">🧠</span> <strong>Mark-and-Sweep Algorithm</strong> - Tracks and cleans up memory when you're not looking</li>
                        <li><span class="emoji">⏱️</span> <strong>Incremental Collection</strong> - No more freezing your app, we're doing this in micro-pauses</li>
                        <li><span class="emoji">👻</span> <strong>Weak References</strong> - For when you want that "situationship" with your objects</li>
                        <li><span class="emoji">📊</span> <strong>Generational Collection</strong> - Young objects die fast, old objects stay winning</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="code-example">
                    <h2>No Memory Leaks, No Problems</h2>
                    <div class="code-block">
                        <div class="code-title">memory_example.csd</div>
                        <pre><code>// You don't need to explicitly free memory
// Just vibe and let the GC handle it

slay createManyObjects(count int) {
    for (sus i = 0; i < count; i++) {
        sus obj = new BigObject();
        // Look ma, no delete!
    }
    // When objects go out of scope, they become candidates for collection
}</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>Memory Management API</h2>
                    <p>While CURSED handles memory automatically, you can still interact with the garbage collector if you're feeling extra:</p>
                    <div class="code-block">
                        <div class="code-title">gc_api.csd</div>
                        <pre><code>yeet "memory/gc";

// Force garbage collection when you're feeling chaotic
slay cleanupBeforeImportantOperation() {
    gc.collectGarbage();
    
    // Get the tea on memory usage
    sus stats = gc.stats();
    console.print("Total allocated: " + stats.totalAllocated);
    
    // Get detailed debug info when things are sus
    sus debug = gc.debugInfo();
}</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="tips">
                    <h2>Bestie Advice 💅</h2>
                    <div class="tips-grid">
                        <div class="tip-card">
                            <div class="tip-icon">💯</div>
                            <h3>Avoid Circular References</h3>
                            <p>Use weak references when objects reference each other in a cycle, or the GC will have to work harder.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tip-card">
                            <div class="tip-icon">⚡</div>
                            <h3>Pool Large Objects</h3>
                            <p>For objects you create and destroy frequently, consider object pooling to reduce GC pressure.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tip-card">
                            <div class="tip-icon">🧩</div>
                            <h3>Implement Traceable</h3>
                            <p>Custom types should implement the Traceable trait so the GC knows how to follow references.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tip-card">
                            <div class="tip-icon">📱</div>
                            <h3>Profile Memory Usage</h3>
                            <p>Use gc.stats() to monitor memory usage and identify potential memory issues.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="faq">
                    <h2>GC FAQ - Spill the Tea ☕</h2>
                    <div class="accordion">
                        <div class="accordion-item">
                            <div class="accordion-header">Will GC make my app slow?</div>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>Not unless you're creating millions of objects per second! CURSED's incremental GC is designed to minimize pauses. Most operations are so fast you won't even notice, fr fr.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="accordion-item">
                            <div class="accordion-header">Can I disable garbage collection?</div>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>No cap, that would be chaotic energy. The GC is a core part of CURSED's memory management. You can tune it, but not disable it entirely.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="accordion-item">
                            <div class="accordion-header">How do I handle resources like files?</div>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>Use the <code>dropz</code> pattern to ensure resources are properly closed. Check the dropz documentation for the tea on resource management.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

